#X text 186 237 period of one sample in ms, f 11;
#X text 37 55 We can use the [vline~] object to generate an impulse. One way is to send the impulse value and schedule the object to go immediately to zero after one sample., f 62;
#X text 23 382 The [float2imp~] is an abstraction from ELSE based on [vline~] \, so it does the conversion from float values to impulses with sample accuracy. Because of the accuracy provided by [vline~] \, it can convert more than one bang within an audio block. Below we convert a float to an impulse whose amplitude corresponds to the float value (1 in this case \, which is also the default value)., f 71;
#X obj 363 294 vline~;
#X msg 363 185 1;
#X obj 363 339 print~;
#X obj 322 262 bng 21 250 50 0 empty empty empty 0 -10 0 12 #dfdfdf #000000 #000000;
#X obj 380 227 delay 1 1 samps;
#X msg 380 251 0;
